        This report was generated using MultiQC, version 1.10.1

        For more information about MultiQC, including other videos and extensive documentation, please visit http://multiqc.info

        Sav-Lane-Metrics-Summary-Table: Columns

        Uncheck the tick box to hide columns. Click and drag the handle on the left to change order.

        Sort Visible Group Column Description ID Scale
        || SAV % >= Q30 Percentage of reads with quality phred score of 30 or above % >= Q30 None
        || SAV Aligned (%) Percentage of reads that aligned to the PhiX genome % Aligned None
        || SAV Clusters (M) Number of clusters for each tile (millions) Cluster Count cluster_count
        || SAV Clusters PF (M) Number of clusters PF for each tile (millions) Cluster Count Pf cluster_count
        || SAV Density The density of clusters (in thousands per mm2) detected by image analysis, +/- 1 standard deviation. Density None
        || SAV Density PF The density of clusters PF (in thousands per mm2) detected by image analysis, +/- 1 standard deviation. Density Pf None
        || SAV Error Rate (%) The calculated error rate, as determined by a PhiX spike-in Error Rate None
        || SAV Error Rate 100 Cycles (%) The calculated error rate for cycles 1-100. Error Rate 100 None
        || SAV Error Rate 35 Cycles (%) The calculated error rate for cycles 1-35. Error Rate 35 None
        || SAV Error Rate 35 Cycles (%) The calculated error rate for cycles 1-50. Error Rate 50 None
        || SAV Error Rate 35 Cycles (%) The calculated error rate for cycles 1-75. Error Rate 75 None
        || SAV Intensity Cycle 1 The average of the A channel intensity measured at the first cycle First Cycle Intensity None
        || SAV M PF Reads The number of passing filter reads (millions) Reads Pf read_count
        || SAV M Reads The number of reads (millions) Reads read_count
        || SAV Occupied (%) The percentage of nanowells occupied by clusters, +/- 1 standard deviation. % Occupied None
        || SAV Phasing The value used by RTA for the percentage of molecules in a cluster for which sequencing falls behind (phasing) the current cycle within a read. Phasing None
        || SAV Phasing Offset The best-fit offset of the phasing corrections, calculated from the entire read. Phasing Offset None
        || SAV Phasing Slope The best-fit slope of the phasing corrections, calculated from the entire read. Phasing Slope None
        || SAV Prephasing The value used by RTA for the percentage of molecules in a cluster for which sequencing jumps ahead (prephasing) the current cycle within a read. Prephasing None
        || SAV Prephasing Offset The best-fit offset of the prephasing corrections, calculated from the entire read. Prephasing Offset None
        || SAV Prephasing Slope The best-fit slope of the prephasing corrections, calculated from the entire read. Prephasing Slope None
        || SAV Projected Yield (Mb) The expected number of bases sequenced (millions base pairs over all 'usable cycles' Projected Yield G base_count
        || SAV Reads PF (%) Percentage of clusters Passing Filter % Pf None
        || SAV Tiles The number of tiles per lane. Tile Count None
        || SAV Yield (M) The number of bases sequenced (millions base pairs over all 'usable cycles' Yield G base_count
